==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Consubstantial
<hw>Con`sub*stan"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>consubstantialis</ets>; <ets>con-</ets> + <ets>substantialis</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>consubstantiel</ets>. See <er>Substantial</er>.]</ety>
<def>Of the same kind or nature; having the same substance or essence;
coessential.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Christ Jesus . . . coeternal and <qex>consubstantial</qex> with
the Father and with the Holy Ghost.</q> <rj><qau>Foxe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consubstantialism</ent>⟦br⟧
